known classes need to be registered, right? I’m contemplating all these loading mechanics and their implications!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test coverage and execution**\\n\\nThe question isn't strictly about native coverage, but it seems tests should run in a native context. I'm thinking about using class literals here. If createContext(String) only relies on the context path, then classLoader.loadClass could construct it based on the package. So, that would mean the dynamic report is covered, which is good! I have to ensure everything aligns correctly with these requirements to make sure the tests fulfill their purpose!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_0ktmzEUYsIcut5IUqakac7Ca|fc_0eb0aa1354b923450169fe442793dc8191b5d0544fdc184e4f", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.glassfish.jaxb/jaxb-xjc/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_glassfish_jaxb/jaxb_xjc/JAXBContextFactoryTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_glassfish_jaxb.jaxb_xjc;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.util.Map;\n\nimport com.sun.tools.xjc.runtime.JAXBContextFactory;\n\nimport jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBContext;\nimport jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBException;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport org_glassfish_jaxb.jaxb_xjc.jaxb_context_factory_model.ObjectFactory;\n\npublic class JAXBContextFactoryTest {\n    private static final Class<?> IMPLEMENTATION_OBJECT_FACTORY =\n            org_glassfish_jaxb.jaxb_xjc.jaxb_context_factory_model.impl.ObjectFactory.class;\n\n    @Test\n    void createContextWithClassesLoadsImplementationObjectFactory() throws JAXBException {\n        JAXBContext context = JAXBContextFactory.createContext(new Class<?>[] {ObjectFactory.class}, Map.of());\n\n        assertThat(context).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(IMPLEMENTATION_OBJECT_FACTORY.getName()).endsWith(\".impl.ObjectFactory\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createContextWithContextPathLoadsImplementationObjectFactory() throws JAXBException {\n        JAXBContext context = JAXBContextFactory.createContext(\n                ObjectFactory.class.getPackageName(), ObjectFactory.class.getClassLoader(), Map.of());\n\n        assertThat(context).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(IMPLEMENTATION_OBJECT_FACTORY.getName()).endsWith(\".impl.ObjectFactory\");\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 907, "output": 1521, "cacheRead": 17920, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20348, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778271251781, "responseId": "resp_0eb0aa1354b923450169fe441474b481918e7cff83d9c10ca0"}}
