type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking about potential context overloads and the expected outcomes. There might be an issue with the support class not being public, which could cause `ClassLoader.loadClass` for the implementation to fail. But do we really need it public? I think it would be better if I edited the setup and removed the support directory altogether. That could simplify things and make the process smoother, right? Let’s go for it.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FD1viwqQ2CoeYvjh2VQexZyp|fc_0eb0aa1354b923450169fe44aed0f081919d08e49713ca52b4", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.glassfish.jaxb/jaxb-xjc/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_glassfish_jaxb/jaxb_xjc/JAXBContextFactoryTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\n\nimport java.util.Map;\n", "newText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatExceptionOfType;\n\nimport java.util.Map;\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org_glassfish_jaxb.jaxb_xjc.jaxb_context_factory_model.ObjectFactory;\n", "newText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n"}, {"oldText": "public class JAXBContextFactoryTest {\n    private static final Class<?> IMPLEMENTATION_OBJECT_FACTORY =\n            org_glassfish_jaxb.jaxb_xjc.jaxb_context_factory_model.impl.ObjectFactory.class;\n    private static final String UNSUPPORTED_PROPERTY_NAME = \"org.example.unsupportedJaxbProperty\";\n    private static final Map<String, Object> UNSUPPORTED_PROPERTIES = Map.of(UNSUPPORTED_PROPERTY_NAME, Boolean.TRUE);\n\n    @Test\n    void createContextWithClassesLoadsImplementationObjectFactory() {\n        assertThat(IMPLEMENTATION_OBJECT_FACTORY.getName()).endsWith(\".impl.ObjectFactory\");\n\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> JAXBContextFactory.createContext(\n                new Class<?>[] {ObjectFactory.class}, UNSUPPORTED_PROPERTIES))\n                .isInstanceOf(JAXBException.class)\n                .hasMessageContaining(UNSUPPORTED_PROPERTY_NAME);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createContextWithContextPathLoadsImplementationObjectFactory() {\n        assertThat(IMPLEMENTATION_OBJECT_FACTORY.getName()).endsWith(\".impl.ObjectFactory\");\n\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> JAXBContextFactory.createContext(\n                ObjectFactory.class.getPackageName(),\n                ObjectFactory.class.getClassLoader(),\n                UNSUPPORTED_PROPERTIES))\n                .isInstanceOf(JAXBException.class)\n                .hasMessageContaining(UNSUPPORTED_PROPERTY_NAME);\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "public class JAXBContextFactoryTest {\n    private static final String IMPLEMENTATION_OBJECT_FACTORY = ObjectFactory.class.getPackageName()\n            + \".impl.ObjectFactory\";\n\n    @Test\n    void createContextWithClassesLoadsImplementationObjectFactory() {\n        assertThatExceptionOfType(JAXBException.class)\n                .isThrownBy(() -> JAXBContextFactory.createContext(new Class<?>[] {ObjectFactory.class}, Map.of()))\n                .satisfies(exception -> assertThat(exception.getLinkedException())\n                        .isInstanceOf(ClassNotFoundException.class)\n                        .hasMessage(IMPLEMENTATION_OBJECT_FACTORY));\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createContextWithContextPathLoadsImplementationObjectFactory() {\n        assertThatExceptionOfType(JAXBException.class)\n                .isThrownBy(() -> JAXBContextFactory.createContext(\n                        ObjectFactory.class.getPackageName(), ObjectFactory.class.getClassLoader(), Map.of()))\n                .satisfies(exception -> assertThat(exception.getLinkedException())\n                        .isInstanceOf(ClassNotFoundException.class)\n                        .hasMessage(IMPLEMENTATION_OBJECT_FACTORY));\n    }\n}\n\nfinal class ObjectFactory {\n    private ObjectFactory() {\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "us